        <h1>Chess Basic Openings</h1>
        
        <h2>White Openings</h2>
        <h3>1.e4 Openings</h3>
        <p>The most popular opening move for White, leading to open and dynamic positions.</p>
        
        <h3>2.d4 Openings</h3>
        <p>A more strategic approach, leading to closed and positional games.</p>
        
        <h2>Black Openings</h2>
        
        <h3>1. Sicilian Defense</h3>
        <p>A popular response to 1.e4, leading to rich counterattacking possibilities.</p>
        
        <h3>2. Traditional Openings</h3>
        <p>Includes openings like the French Defense and the Caro-Kann.</p>
        
        <h3>3. Setup Based Openings</h3>
        <p>These involve setting up pieces in a particular structure rather than following strict move orders.</p>
        
        <h3>4. Building Blocks Openings</h3>
        <p>These focus on fundamental principles such as center control and piece development.</p>
        
        <h2>Caro-Kann Defense</h2>
        
        <h3>1. Caro-Kann: Classical Variation</h3>
        <p>A solid response by Black, aiming for long-term strategic play.</p>
        <img src="D:\Chess\Openings\Caro-Kann Defense Classical Variation.jpeg" alt="Caro-Kann Defense Classical Variation">
        
        <h3>2. Caro-Kann: Advance Variation</h3>
        <p>White gains space in the center early on, leading to sharp play.</p>
